messages.content: My nephew goes to Morton! I went to school in Hammond but I went to Clark, not Morton. I can't speak much for the school because I don't know it too well. I would say the area isn't fantastic, but it is close to Chicago like you want! Just from what I hear from my nephew, I would think you would have to be strong/strict, but there is no reason why you couldn't have a good time there! Plus, they pay well!
Morton High School. Know anything about it? Did you go to school in Hammond?

Oh I bet they had already filled the positions by that time! Must not have been meant to be. Oh Hammond? I used to live there. What school? But that's seems like a better fit if you want to be close to Chicago!
I thought the interview went alright, but I didn't get a call a call back from them. Which is fine, because I think I'm going to take a job in Hammond anyway. I want to be a little closer to Chicago.
Hey! I never got to talk to you after your interview at Merrillville. How did it go? Have you made any decisions about where you'll be next year?
You are now connected on Messenger.
